<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 97-03-05 - Vari-Rate Spring Suspension Seats and U-Bolt Plates Used With Spicer Axles</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi970305" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>97-03-05</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>November, 1997</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>SPRINGS</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Vari-Rate Spring Suspension Seats and U-Bolt Plates Used With Spicer Axles</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4400</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Navistar has redesigned the attaching hardware for the 4x2 vari-rate spring suspension used with
                    Spicer axles. The redesigned hardware will provide improved U-bolt clamp load retention and
                    joint/housing integrity for today's higher torque engines. The new spring seats and U-bolt plates
                    are contoured for the Spicer axle cold formed housing design and will not fit Eaton or Rockwell axle
                    housings.
                </para>
                <para>The current hardware will continue to be used on the hot formed Eaton and Rockwell axle
                    housings.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
